modules.description: This module provides a map structure with ordered keys, supporting operations like insertion, deletion, ordered traversal (e.g., `min_binding`, `find_first`), merging, and polymorphic value transformations. It works with maps where keys are strings and values are arbitrary types, offering bidirectional conversion to sequences, filtering, partitioning, and ordered iteration. It is suited for scenarios requiring efficient key-based queries and ordered data aggregation, such as time zone data management or sorted key-value storage.

This module manages time zone data with efficient key-based queries and ordered data traversal. It provides a map structure for string keys and polymorphic values, supporting insertion, deletion, ordered iteration, and bidirectional conversion to sequences. It is used for time zone data aggregation and sorted key-value storage.
